	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just spent a good few hours in The Warrens today.&nbsp;&nbsp;Me and a buddy checked various places, first the chef and smithy, but they dropped nothing useful.  Then we went to the prince, he was a slow spawn and after 3 kills and no drops, we left.  We then came into the Throne Room, spent around 3 hours there.  High Shaman was blue at 23, and the King was yellow.  He was not too strong in melee when he was alone, but good luck with that.  When you attack the king, he first HTs for 250 dmg, then he runs to you, but not straight to you, he hugs the wall behind him and then passes by the room where the lorekeeper is at, then heads to you.  In his little parade to get to you, he often pulls everything in the area with him.  He is not a hard fight for a group of high teens low 20s, but the adds are killer.  And everything in the area will aggro on ya, no matter how green.  We killed King 3 times in 3 hours, so I'm guessing he's an hourly spawn, and we received a cold iron helmet and mask and then nothing worth while the 3rd time.  I'd love to stay and camp him, but keeping the area clear is a real pain, and when you get the High Shaman with him, it's real rough.  Hope this helps someone!<br><br>23rd Bard on Saryn<br><br>BTW, if you're in there just for the loot, killing the surronding kobolds will generate lots of soft wicker armor, in those 3 hours we got about 2 full suits.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
